    "timestamp": "2024-07-07T00:01",
    "place": null,
    "description": "days: day 11, jul 7 (dinosaur pp, ab -> west glacier, mt)\ntime: 00:01\ndate: 2024-07-07\nwoke up at our campsite in dinosaur provincial park. drove impossibly straight and flat roads up to closer to 52 than 51 north latitude before rotating 90 degrees at hanna on the way to drumheller. from there we went to calgary, one of those canadian island metropolises with nothing around it but a mountain backdrop in this case. stopped downtown for lunch at a pretty fancy restaurant with open walls and then left for montana. drove the deerhoof trail -- intermittently a highway, at times the main thoroughfare of small towns -- back to the border, eagerly anticipating the ride across glacier national park along going to the sun highway. it was better than anticipated. steep walls, incredible vistas, waterfalls dressing the inner wall.",
